This doesn't fit with my personal taste in SCP entries. I enjoy SCP mainly as a series of stories in a shared universe about the SCP Foundation, a vaguely realistic quasi-governmental organisation in our modern world, where there are always some threads between SCP and things that are happening in everyday life. I'm not really interested in stories from the future, or fantasy universes, especially when they dump lots of backstory that has no connection to the rest of SCP - I mean, I don't mind reading stories about these things, I just go elsewhere other than this website to read them.

However, I mainly just say this because this was an exception that held my attention the whole way through, and in spite of the above easily got an upvote, so good job. It's rare that I read anything that basically creates a whole setting in a massive backstory dump while remaining readable, which is a testament to your writing skill.

also, is this Sunless Skies inspired, because it feels very Sunless Skies, (which I think is complimentary)





